name: Collectors Spode Cushion
description:
Launched in 1816, Blue Italia is one of the collections that secured Spode's reputation as a leader in the ceramic industry; it is now one of Spode's most collected ranges and is still made to this day. 

The Spode fabric is not in print anymore, and i managed to get hold of literal scraps from the States.. 

2 cushions available 22"x22" duck filled cushions.. with a complimentary patchwork of brown poker dot, Navy, Denim, rust shot Taffeta fabric and the stunning Spode fabric inset.. piped and backed in denim.

name: Dysfunctional family meets country folk
description:
Freehand design. The front of the cushion has been put together using the retro 'pop' comic Michael Miller fabric 'dysfunctional families', (I think the caption about arsenic did it for me, 1950's humour), combined with strips of red poker dot cotton, multi coloured bubble cotton, denim and tweed.  All connected with a tweed piping around the edge.  On the back: retro dysfunctional families fabric, framed by the tweed piping. 

Comes with 16"x16"  Duck feather filled cushion pad and the price includes postage.
Overseas postage will vary.. please email georgette1marshall@yahoo.co.uk
